4. Newsletter and email compliance
CAN-SPAM (US) requires: clear identification, physical address, and one-click unsubscribe in every commercial email. GDPR/PECR (EU) requires explicit opt-in for marketing emails. For a US-only MVP, opt-in defaults to TRUE (CAN-SPAM compliant) but this must be reviewed before any EU expansion. The design implements one-click unsubscribe via signed JWT token — no account required to unsubscribe, immediate effect, with resubscribe option.

Transactional vs marketing email distinction — CRITICAL
TRANSACTIONAL (always send regardless of preferences): order_confirmation, order_shipped, order_delivered, sla_delay_alert, magic_link. These are required for the purchase contract.
MARKETING (check newsletter_opt_in first): campaign_updates, coffee_tips, impact_reports. Skip silently if opt_in=false.
sendEmail() in packages/email must enforce this distinction. Pass an email category param. Fail loudly (throw) if a TRANSACTIONAL email is accidentally suppressed.
List-Unsubscribe header: add to all marketing emails via Resend headers param. Gmail and Apple Mail show a one-click unsubscribe option natively.

5. Stripe Customer Portal scope
The Stripe Customer Portal is used exclusively for payment method management. It cannot show Joe Perks order history, tracking, or fundraiser impact — those live in the Joe Perks database. Buyers access the portal via a "Manage payment methods" button — they are never sent to Stripe directly without an explicit click. The portal is configured in Stripe Dashboard with subscriptions disabled (Joe Perks has none) and payment method management enabled.

6. Account deletion and GDPR right to erasure
Account deletion anonymises the Buyer.email field to preserve Order foreign keys for financial audit. The buyer_id is retained internally. All Buyer PII (name, email) is cleared. This satisfies the GDPR right to erasure without corrupting the order history that's needed for Stripe reconciliation and dispute evidence. Order records are never deleted.

