Acceptance Criteria
#
Acceptance Criteria
AC1
GET /account/sign-in: single email input, "Send me a sign-in link" CTA, no password field
AC2
On submit: MagicLink created (purpose=BUYER_AUTH, expires_at=now+15min), sendEmail(buyer_auth_magic_link) sent via packages/email
AC3
If email has NO Buyer record: show "We don't have an account for that email. Have you placed an order?" with link to /order-lookup
AC4
Confirmation screen after submit: "Check your email — we sent a link to [email]. It expires in 15 minutes." — do not confirm whether the email exists (prevents enumeration)
AC5
GET /account/auth/[token]: validates token (exists, not expired, not used_at, purpose=BUYER_AUTH)
AC6
On valid token: used_at set atomically before any further action; Buyer.last_sign_in_at updated; session cookie set (HttpOnly, Secure, SameSite=Lax, 30-day expiry)
AC7
Session cookie payload: { buyer_id, iat } — signed HS256 JWT using SESSION_SECRET
AC8
redirect param preserved: /account/auth/[token]?redirect=/account/orders/[id] redirects there on success
AC9
Expired/used token: "This link has expired — links are valid for 15 minutes. Request a new one." with link to /account/sign-in
AC10
Sign out: DELETE /api/account/session — clears cookie, redirects to /, shows "You've been signed out" toast
AC11
Rate limiting: 5 magic link requests/hour/IP via Upstash (reuses US-01-09)
AC12
Magic link email subject: "Sign in to Joe Perks" — plain, recognisable, not spammy

Technical Notes
	•	Use iron-session or jose library for JWT cookie signing — not a raw cookie with buyer_id
	•	Token validation uses atomic DB update: UPDATE MagicLink SET used_at=now() WHERE id=X AND used_at IS NULL RETURNING id — if 0 rows returned, token already used
	•	Email enumeration: always show the "Check your email" screen regardless of whether the email exists — prevents account discovery
	•	Magic link email must render correctly in Gmail, Apple Mail, and Outlook — test with React Email dev server

UX / Design Notes
	•	Sign-in page is deliberately minimal — one field, one button. No surrounding nav or footer that distracts.
	•	After submit, show a mail icon animation or illustration — something warm and reassuring while they open email
	•	"Resend link" option appears after 30 seconds on the confirmation screen — prevents frustrated repeat submits
	•	The email itself: large, thumb-friendly button in brand green. Single purpose — sign in. No other links or marketing content in this email.
	•	Mobile: auto-focus the email input on page load. Use inputType="email" for correct keyboard on mobile.

Definition of Done
	•	Sign-in email received within 10s
	•	Link redirects to /account with session cookie set
	•	Same link clicked twice shows expired message
	•	Sign-out clears cookie

