so that repeat purchases for the causes I support take seconds, not minutes

Dependencies: US-09-02  ·  US-09-00
Acceptance Criteria
#
Acceptance Criteria
AC1
On Buyer creation (US-05-01 webhook upsert): stripe.customers.create({ email, name, metadata: { buyer_id } }) — store stripe_customer_id on Buyer. Wrapped in try/catch — failure creates Buyer without stripe_customer_id.
AC2
Buyer.stripe_customer_id is nullable — guest orders and any orders where Stripe Customer creation failed proceed normally without saved payment methods.
AC3
PaymentIntent for signed-in buyers: created with customer=buyer.stripe_customer_id and setup_future_usage="off_session" — enables Stripe to save the card if buyer opts in.
AC4
Checkout Step 3 for signed-in buyers with stripe_customer_id: Payment Element (replaces CardElement) renders with saved cards enabled. Saved cards shown with last 4 digits, expiry, and card brand icon.
AC5
"Save this card for future orders" checkbox on Step 3 — UNCHECKED by default. When unchecked, payment_method_save="disabled" on PaymentIntent.
AC6
Guest checkout Step 3: Payment Element without customer param — no card saving. Existing behaviour unchanged.
AC7
customer.updated Stripe webhook: received and acknowledged — no DB action required. Stripe handles payment method management.
AC8
Saved card removal available via Stripe Customer Portal (US-09-09).
AC9
If stripe_customer_id is set but Stripe Customer no longer exists (deleted): catch the error, clear Buyer.stripe_customer_id, proceed as guest checkout.

Technical Notes
	•	Payment Element replaces CardElement across all checkouts — it is backwards compatible and handles saved cards gracefully when no customer is passed.
	•	setup_future_usage: "off_session" on PaymentIntent tells Stripe to save the card even if buyer navigates away after payment succeeds.
	•	"Save this card" UX: pass payment_method_save param to Stripe Payment Element options — Stripe handles the actual saving UI/confirmation natively.
	•	Stripe Customer creation failure: log to Sentry but do NOT block order creation. Order proceeds without saved payment method capability.

UX / Design Notes
	•	"Save this card" must be opt-in — never default-checked. This is both a UX best practice and a legal requirement in many jurisdictions.
	•	Show a "Secured by Stripe" trust badge and padlock icon adjacent to the "Save this card" checkbox.
	•	Saved cards should show the card brand logo (Visa/MC/Amex) alongside last 4 and expiry — buyers identify their card by visual brand, not by number.
	•	If a buyer has multiple saved cards, show the most recently used first with a "Default" label.

Definition of Done
	•	Signed-in buyer with saved card sees it pre-filled at checkout
	•	"Save this card" unchecked: no card saved after payment
	•	Stripe Customer visible in Stripe test dashboard after first order
	•	Guest checkout unchanged — no Payment Element with saved cards

